	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Retrode adapter boards exist for Atari 2600 and GBC, both of which use mappers. A Retrode adapter board designed for common NES mappers would probably plug into the Genesis port, with both PRG and CHR address connected to Genesis address, CHR D0-D7 connected to Genesis D8-D15, and PRG D0-D7 connected to Genesis D0-D7.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


